# Wayfinder — Team Standards

## Language & Runtime
- Python 3.11 only
- All functions must have type hints
- No `print()` — use `structlog` for logging (or `print(f"[module] msg")` pattern for hackathon speed)
- No `requests` without explicit timeout parameter

## Frameworks
- Agent orchestrator: FastAPI
- Testing: pytest
- Linting: ruff
- No Flask, no Django (FastAPI only)

## Security (non-negotiable)
- No plaintext secrets in code or config files
- `.env` is gitignored — never commit it
- All LLM tool calls must go through the allow-list in `agent/tool_registry.py`
- No `http_get` or outbound URL tool exposed to the LLM
- All CoT emitted by the agent must be signed via `crypto/cot_signer.py`
- All CoT received must be verified via `crypto/cot_signer.py` before forwarding to ATAK

## Directory ownership (CODEOWNERS enforced)
- Only touch your own directory unless paired
- Cross-directory changes require paired reviewer from §13 of PRD

## Commit style (lefthook enforced)
- `feat(agent): description`
- `fix(routing): description`
- `security(crypto): description`
- `chore(infra): description`

## Definition of Done
A change is done when: `make ci` passes locally AND on the PR.
